&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nycandre/4657806509/" title="The fish are in a crummy mood"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4022/4657806509_629f8c317a_m.jpg" width="240" height="158" alt="The fish are in a crummy mood" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Monkfish aka &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglerfish" rel="nofollow"&gt;Anglerfish  &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/8177037@N06/"&gt;stevesheriw&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8177037@N06/4664576457/" title="&amp;quot;Top Kill Fails&amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4025/4664576457_deb0bd51df_m.jpg" width="240" height="161" alt="&amp;quot;Top Kill Fails&amp;quot;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A sign of the times while visiting New Orleans.  This was the largest oil spill in history, and New Orleans is the closest major city.  While oil itself has not intruded into New Orleans, it is causing damage to the fishing industry.  At this time, the long term effect of the spill is uncertain.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;quot;Top Kill&amp;quot; refers to the latest effort to contain the spill, and today there was not good news.&lt;/p&gt;

