&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/usfwssoutheast/"&gt;USFWS/Southeast&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/usfwssoutheast/4685315854/" title="Saving an oiled bird's life"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1308/4685315854_4297b77a24_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Saving an oiled bird's life" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JEFFERSON PARISH, La.--Kayla DiBenedetto of the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service carries an oiled pelican from a nesting area where she netted it in Barataria Bay to a waiting boat on Saturday, June 5, 2010. The pelican was transported to a stabilization facility on Grand Isle, La., and was later taken to the Oiled Wildlife Rehabilitation Center in Fort Jackson, La. Federal and state wildlife officials are working together on a daily basis to rescue birds, mammals and reptiles affected by the Deepwater Horizon oil spill. &lt;a href="http://www.fws.gov/home/dhoilspill/" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.fws.gov/home/dhoilspill/&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Coast Guard Photo by Petty Officer 2nd Class John D. Miller.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/usfwssoutheast/"&gt;USFWS/Southeast&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/usfwssoutheast/4685381274/" title="Brown pelicans aren't supposed to be this brown..."&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4007/4685381274_465cacbbcb_m.jpg" width="159" height="240" alt="Brown pelicans aren't supposed to be this brown..." /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JEFFERSON PARISH, La. – Jeff Phillips, Environmental Contaminants Coordinator for the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service, rescues a Brown Pelican from the Barataria Bay in Grand Isle, La., June 4, 2010. State and federal wildlife services pulled approximately 60 Brown Pelicans, in the last two days, covered in oil from the Barataria Bay area. &lt;a href="http://www.fws.gov/home/dhoilspill/" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.fws.gov/home/dhoilspill/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
U.S. Coast Guard photo by Petty Officer 3rd Class Ann Marie Gorden.&lt;/p&gt;

