&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/patrick-smith-photography/4711475459/" title="In memory of the US Gulf Coast - Grayton Beach, Florida"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4029/4711475459_2ac0743bbc_m.jpg" width="240" height="160" alt="In memory of the US Gulf Coast - Grayton Beach, Florida" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Winter 2008, here are the sparkling white sands of the US Gulf coast!  (With tea colored water from an estuary flowing by.) This beach in the Florida Panhandle near Destin is still clean as of June 18, 2010, but the oil is creeping to within 40 miles (60km).  This location is hundreds of miles from the well of the BP oil spill. No HDR.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
See the 1200 pixel version!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/patrick-smith-photography/4711475459/sizes/o/"&gt;www.flickr.com/photos/patrick-smith-photography/471147545...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Go to &lt;a href="http://flickr.com/people/patrick-smith-photography/"&gt;My profile &lt;/a&gt; for:&lt;br /&gt;
* a link to my website,&lt;br /&gt;
* licensing (No Getty!),&lt;br /&gt;
* to follow me on Twitter,&lt;br /&gt;
* for small group workshop information, and to sign up for my free monthly newsletter.  &lt;br /&gt;
  (I will talk about theories and techniques.  No spam will be sent!)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
