&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/usnavynvns/4754373235/" title="Secretary of the Navy Ray Mabus meets with legislators and community leaders. "&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4080/4754373235_c2712c41a2_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Secretary of the Navy Ray Mabus meets with legislators and community leaders. " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
BILOXI, Miss. (June 30, 2010) Secretary of the Navy (SECNAV) the Honorable Ray Mabus addresses legislators, mayors and community leaders during a town hall meeting in Biloxi, Miss. to discuss the Deepwater Horizon oil spill on Gulf Coast states. Mabus is on a five-day visit to the Gulf Coast to assess the area to develop a long-term restoration plan for the region. He will meet with state and local officials in Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama and Florida. (U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Kevin S. O'Brien/Released) 100630-N-5549O-099&lt;/p&gt;

