&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/usnavynvns/4754373379/" title="Secretary of the Navy Ray Mabus conducts a press briefing. "&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4075/4754373379_932927bac3_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Secretary of the Navy Ray Mabus conducts a press briefing. " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
JACKSON, Miss. (June 30, 2010) Secretary of the Navy (SECNAV) the Honorable Ray Mabus, right, and Mississippi Gov. Haley Barbour address media after a meeting discussing the impact of the Deepwater Horizon oil spill on Gulf Coast states. Mabus is on a five-day visit to the Gulf Coast to assess the area to develop a long-term restoration plan for the region. He will meet with state and local officials in Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama and Florida. (U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Kevin S. O'Brien/Released) 100630-N-5549O-030&lt;/p&gt;

