&lt;p&gt;Boat driver Faye Lewis, left, manuevers an inflatable as Medic Val Kharchenko gets a line on floats attached to an environmental acoustic recording system in the Gulf of Mexico near the Deepwater Horizon spill site, prior to being brought aboard the Greenpeace ship MY Arctic Sunrise October 5, 2010. Scientists from the University of Louisiana at Lafayette, the University of Southern Mississippi and experts from Omni Technologies Inc., returned to the deployment sites to retrieve the acoustic recording systems that have been anchored to the ocean floor recording whales sounds for the past three weeks. The data will be compared with previous studies done in the same location.  Photo by Robert Meyers/Greenpeace&lt;br /&gt;
