&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/unquiet/5132655395/" title="What He Said!"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1382/5132655395_2773a883f1_m.jpg" width="240" height="240" alt="What He Said!" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just as I was taking this picture on my way back up from the store - my cat played King of the Hill with my Nikon ($$$ to replace/fix) and an expensive lens after someone placed it on the cat's favorite chair.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I had to perform delicate emergency surgery on the lens ring, but she (the camera, not the cat; the cat's fine) is going to pull through. The battery pack ($140 MD-80) has got a signifcant crack in its body but seems structurally sound... its door is still busted but a little tape will keep that closed for now. The Sigma DC 18-50mm f/2.8 EX Macro (a $400+ lens) survived without a scratch. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Whew.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
P.S. BP, clean that shit up!&lt;/p&gt;

